Sentencas: Anode-supported planar solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with dimension from 5 x 5 cm(2) to 15 x 15 cm(2) have been successfully fabricated by tape casting, screen-printing and single-step co-firing technologies, which shows a potential way of cost-effective for mass production.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance evaluation of planar solid oxide fuel cell with large active reaction area

Sentencas: The performance of the cells has been investigated at operating temperature between 650 degrees C and 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance evaluation of planar solid oxide fuel cell with large active reaction area

Sentencas: The typical cell with dimension of 10 x 10 cm(2) (active reaction area of 9 x 9 cm(2)) obtained open circuit voltage (OCV) of 1.15 V and power density of 770 mW/cm(2) at current density of 950 mA/cm(2) at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance evaluation of planar solid oxide fuel cell with large active reaction area

Sentencas: The performance degradation of the cell is lower than 1.56%/1000 h. When external reformed methane gas was used as fuel, the cell showed no obvious performance decrease compared to that using pure hydrogen as fuel.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance evaluation of planar solid oxide fuel cell with large active reaction area

Sentencas: The test results have demonstrated that the as-prepared large size cells have excellent performance and reliability, which is ready for SOFC stack assembly.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance evaluation of planar solid oxide fuel cell with large active reaction area
